44128.description:
You have been enlisted as a Naval Capsuleer.
Standard equipment is issued to all naval capsuleers and your combat ship and gear is included in this container.
Once opened, this container will self-destruct.
Gear is delivered to your Item Hangar while your frigates will be safely delivered to your Ship Hangar for your immediate use.
44128.name: Naval Capsuleer Starter Pack

45584.description:
This Hyasyoda Research Lab Technical Data Chip holds specifications and proprietary nano-assembler instructions for upgraded Hyasyoda corporation research facilities.

It should theoretically be possible for a talented capsuleer to interface with this data chip and recover usable blueprint data.
45584.name: Technical Data Chip

fixed.description: This package contains fireworks. Handle with care.

45585.description:
This Thukker Capital Component Manufacturing Technical Data Chip holds specifications and proprietary nano-assembler instructions for advanced black market Thukker capital component manufacturing upgrades.

It should theoretically be possible for a talented capsuleer to interface with this data chip and recover usable blueprint data.
45585.name: Technical Data Chip

46601.description:
This armored and electromagnetically hardened data cache is normally integrated into the Guristas shipyard facilities, providing a high level of security and protection from corruption while building Loggerhead-class Force Auxiliaries.

These armored caches have a good chance of surviving the destruction of the facility they are installed in. If recovered by suitable ships, the caches can be accessed and the Loggerhead blueprint data recovered.
46601.name: Guristas Loggerhead Blueprint Armored Cache

46454.description:
This pack contains a Caldari Cormorant destroyer and a selection of modules.

The Cormorant is the only State-produced space vessel whose design has come from a third party. 
Rumors abound, of course, but the designer's identity has remained a tightly-kept secret in the State's inner circle.
46454.name: Cormorant Destroyer Battle Pack

46455.description:
This pack contains a Gallente Catalyst destroyer and a selection of modules.

Ideally suited for both skirmish warfare and fleet support, the Catalyst is touted as one of the best anti-frigate platforms out there. 
Faced with its top-of-the-line tracking equipment, not many can argue.
46455.name: Catalyst Destroyer Battle Pack

46456.description:
This pack contains a Minmatar Thrasher destroyer and a selection of modules.

Engineered as a supplement to its big brother the Cyclone, the Thrasher's tremendous turret capabilities and advanced tracking computers allow it to protect its larger counterpart from smaller, faster menaces.
46456.name: Thrasher Destroyer Battle Pack

46457.description: This package has been awarded for your swift and decisive actions on behalf of the State Military Stockpile corporation.
46457.name: Caracal State Military Stockpile Pack

46450.description: This package has been awarded for your just and righteous actions on behalf of the Imperial War Reserves corporation.
46450.name: Apocalypse Imperial War Reserves Pack

46451.description:
This pack contains a Venture mining frigate and a selection of modules.

Recognizing the dire need for a ship capable of fast operation in unsafe territories, ORE created the Venture.
It was conceived as a vessel primed and ready for any capsuleer, no matter how new to the dangers of New Eden they might be, who wishes to engage in the respectable trade of mining.

The Venture has amazing abilities to quickly drill through to the ores and gases it's after, harvesting them at the speed necessary for mining in hostile space, and getting out relatively unscathed.
46451.name: Venture Mining Pack

46452.description:
This pack contains a Procurer and a selection of modules that can be equipped to mining barges.

Mining barges are the next step up from the Venture, with much higher mining yields, larger ore bays and/or a stronger tank. 
Also, in contrast to the Venture, the mining barges can fit strip miners (with much higher yield than normal mining modules) and ice miners. 

There are three mining barges, each optimized for a different role: The Procurer, the Covetor and the Retriever.
46452.name: Procurer Mining Barge Pack

46453.description:
This pack contains an Amarr Coercer destroyer and a selection of modules.

Noticing the alarming increase in Minmatar frigate fleets, the Imperial Navy made its plans for the Coercer, a vessel designed specifically to seek and destroy the droves of fast-moving frigate rebels.
46453.name: Coercer Destroyer Battle Pack

48761.description: This Triglavian trinary data vault was obtained by inputting Triglavian survey data into a Bioadaptive Cache in Abyssal Deadspace. The contents of the output data vault seem to vary according to some inscrutable formula that presumably depends on the contents of the inputted survey data. Alternatively, the output may simply be determined by a probabilistic exchange algorithm that only a Triglavian would understand.
48761.name: Triglavian Cache Data Vault

45677.description:
This armored and electromagnetically hardened data cache is normally integrated into the Blood Raider Covenant's shipyard facilities, providing a high level of security and protection from corruption while building Molok-class Titans.

These armored caches have a good chance of surviving the destruction of the facility they are installed in. If recovered by suitable ships, the caches can be accessed and the Molok blueprint data recovered.
45677.name: Blood Raider Molok Blueprint Armored Cache

46260.description:
This package has been awarded to you by your mentor to accelerate your capsuleer training.
Inside you will find skill books that when trained, will allow you to operate various ships.

This meticulously constructed strong box is hermetically sealed with a robust electronic locking mechanism which provides a perfect level of internal preservation.
However, compromising this seal will have devastating effects on the container, causing it to fully disintegrate.

Despite that, the integrity of the items held within is retained, keeping them safe for future use.

43930.description:
This package has been awarded for your just and righteous actions on behalf of the Amarr Empire.

This meticulously constructed strong box is hermetically sealed with a robust electronic locking mechanism which provides a perfect level of internal preservation.

However, compromising this seal will have devastating effects on the container, causing it to fully disintegrate.

Despite that, the integrity of the items held within is retained, keeping them safe for future use.
